flowchart TB
    Start[Insurer offers<br/>flat premium with<br/>no risk classification<br/>Premium = 1,000 USD]

    Start --> Demand{Who shows up<br/>to buy?}

    Demand -->|Expected loss 300| LowRisk[Low-risk applicant<br/>'This is overpriced for me'<br/>Declines to buy]
    Demand -->|Expected loss 1,000| AvgRisk[Average-risk applicant<br/>'Price is about right'<br/>Buys]
    Demand -->|Expected loss 2,500| HighRisk[High-risk applicant<br/>'This is a bargain!'<br/>Rushes to buy]

    LowRisk --> PoolA[Pool composition shifts]
    AvgRisk --> PoolA
    HighRisk --> PoolA

    PoolA --> Losses[Actual loss ratio<br/>exceeds 100%<br/>Insurer loses money]

    Losses --> Response{Insurer response}

    Response -->|Raise rates| RaiseRates[Rate increased<br/>to 1,500 USD]
    RaiseRates --> Exit[Remaining average risks<br/>now consider it overpriced<br/>They exit]
    Exit --> WorsePool[Pool now only highest risks]
    WorsePool --> MoreLosses[Loss ratio worsens again]
    MoreLosses --> Response

    Response -->|Classify risks<br/>differently| Classify[Apply risk classification<br/>Low-risk: 400<br/>Average: 1,000<br/>High-risk: 2,500]
    Classify --> Stable[Stable pool<br/>Each class pays fair price<br/>Adverse selection averted]

    Response -->|Do nothing| Spiral[DEATH SPIRAL<br/>Pool collapses]

    style Start fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#e65100,stroke-width:2px
    style HighRisk fill:#ffcdd2,stroke:#b71c1c,stroke-width:2px
    style LowRisk fill:#c8e6c9,stroke:#1b5e20
    style Spiral fill:#b71c1c,color:#fff,stroke:#b71c1c,stroke-width:3px
    style Stable fill:#c8e6c9,stroke:#1b5e20,stroke-width:3px
    style Classify fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#0d47a1,stroke-width:2px
